"O should play f5, f3, f4, then f6 or f2 in that order.  Each of the first two moves by O forces a win if X does not respond by blocking the winning move. O, can then follow up with f5 or f3 depending on the first move to force another blocking move.  The third move of f4 by O would then create two winning possibilities.  Since X can only respond with one blocking move, O will win in its fourth move by either playing f6 or f2 depending on the third move by X."
